The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, February 13, 2004 				 Samsung recasts local operations
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Feb. 12: Samsung Electronics is shifting its management structure in Asia as the technology leader readies for growth in the region.																								Under the new structure, India, which was previously under Samsung Southeast Asia, will now be the hub for Samsung Southwest Asia covering all Saarc markets, excluding Pakistan.																								Kwang-Soo Kim, former president and CEO of Samsung Southeast Asia, has been appointed as the first president and CEO of Samsung Southwest Asia operations. He will also continue to function as managing director of Samsung India Electronics.																								India has been identified as one of our six global strategic markets and Southwest Asia region is poised to play an increasingly bigger role in our global business in the near future, said K. S. Kim after assuming the charge as regional president and CEO. 
